subjective.chief_complaint: Dry itchy skin on chest and back
subjective.hpi: 47-year-old patient presents with a 4-day history of dry, itchy skin on the chest and back. Symptoms include soreness and cracking. No bleeding, discharge, or spread to other areas. Patient has tried over-the-counter steroid cream last night with minimal effect and antihistamines. No fever, vomiting, shortness of breath, or cough. Patient believes the symptoms are related to eczema and has no serious concerns.
symptoms: Dry itchy skin on chest and back

plan.patient_instructions: Review in 10-14 days if no improvement or earlier if concerns or worsening
